{
  "_comment": [
    "Default OAuth-service catalog shipped with every DMH-AI release.",
    "Pre-populates the oauth_catalog table on first install so operators",
    "see a populated table in the admin UI immediately. Every entry is",
    "`enabled: false` with empty client_id / client_secret — the operator",
    "registers their own OAuth app at the provider's developer console,",
    "pastes the credentials into the admin UI, and flips Enabled.",
    "",
    "Endpoints below are the provider's standard OAuth 2.x URLs at the",
    "time of release. Operators can edit them in the admin UI if a",
    "provider rotates URLs or if a per-tenant subdomain is needed",
    "(Mailchimp, Auth0, Okta, Salesforce per-instance).",
    "",
    "scopes_default values are sensible read-only starting points.",
    "Operators tune them to match the access their app actually needs.",
    "OIDC-style providers (google, slack, salesforce, linkedin) carry",
    "`openid email profile` so the post-callback userinfo fetch can",
    "identify the account in one trip — bumping the user's consent",
    "into the same dialog as the data scopes. Non-OIDC providers use",
    "their native account-aware scope (e.g. github read:user, slack",
    "users:read).",
    "",
    "extra_auth_params encode known per-provider quirks that need to",
    "ride on the authorization URL (e.g. Google's access_type=offline,",
    "Atlassian's audience=api.atlassian.com).",
    "",
    "userinfo_endpoint + userinfo_field_path drive multi-account",
    "support: after token exchange the OAuth callback GETs the URL",
    "with the access token and reads the account identifier (typically",
    "the email or login) at the dotted JSON path. NULL on either field",
    "= we don't know how to identify accounts on this provider; the",
    "credential row stores account='' (the legacy single-account",
    "default) and lookup_creds returns it like any other row."
  ],

  "services": [
    {
      "slug":                   "google",
      "display_name":           "Google APIs (Calendar / Gmail / Drive / etc.)",
      "host_match":             "googleapis.com",
      "authorization_endpoint": "https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/v2/auth",
      "token_endpoint":         "https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token",
      "scopes_default":         [
        "openid",
        "email",
        "profile",
        "https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar.readonly",
        "https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly",
        "https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.readonly"
      ],
      "extra_auth_params":      { "access_type": "offline", "prompt": "consent" },
      "extra_token_params":     {},
      "userinfo_endpoint":      "https://openidconnect.googleapis.com/v1/userinfo",
      "userinfo_field_path":    "email",
      "client_id":              "",
      "client_secret":          null,
      "enabled":                false
    },

